What are the four steps in the Assessment Methodologies & Measures Overview?
A. Search, Assess, Sell, Service
B. Qualify, Assess, Analyze, Design
C. Interview, Discover, Define, Design
D. Qualify, Assess, Discover, Design
Answer: A
Which elements are correctly paired with their respective steps in the flow as provided in
the Assessment Methodologies & Measures Overview? (Select two.)
A. Assess - Company Tour
B. Assess - Discovery & Design
C. Analyze - Managed Environment Assessment
D. Design - Business Case
E. Analyze - Business Case
Answer: A,B
Which statement is true about the “Elements of a Corporate Strategy”? (Select two.)
A. The “objective” is the aspiration of an organization.
B. The “mission” is the quantification or specification of a goal.
C. The “goal” is the general statement of aim or purpose.
D. The “strategy” is a long-term direction or measure.
E. The “vision” is the overriding purpose
Answer: B,C

You are on a company tour at customer's site and you notice that stacks of consumables
are placed next to printing devices or in separate rooms. What are possible pain
points/risks of this practice? (Select two.)
A. risk of expiring/non-compatible consumables
B. high storage costs
C. lack of remote device management
D. insufficient service level agreements
Answer: A,B
What typically happens if an organization focuses on reducing cost-per-page (CPP)?
A. The overall printing costs can be reduced.
B. The TCO can increase.
C. The total costs stay the same as other factors automatically increase
D. The CPP cannot be reduced without reducing the TCO
Answer: A

According to Gartner market research, what is the largest contributor (cost category) within
the TCO approach?
a. hardware including cost of financing
b. supplies (toner/ink)
c. service and maintenance
d. IT operations
Answer: A
You are on a company tour at a customer's site and you notice that most of the devices are
locally/PC-connected and low-end models. What are the possible impacts of this situation?
(Select three.)
A. Locally connected devices typically have more consumables to stock
B. Document processes are impacted by printing to locally connected devices.
C. Desktop/personal devices often have fewer features and minor performance.
D. No central or remote printer management is possible.
E. Personal/desktop printers generally have higher costs per page
Answer: C,D,E
